User Guide: Ecotone Mobile (Android)

Table of Contents:

1. Introduction
2. Installation
3. Setup
4. Usage
5. Troubleshooting
6. Conclusion

1. Introduction:
Ecotone Mobile is a mobile application designed to assist Biology and Resource Management students at OSU Cascades in identifying native plants, locating sites (plots), and tracking the long-term trends of the ecotone on the OSU Cascades campus. This user guide aims to provide comprehensive instructions for users to effectively navigate and utilize Ecotone Mobile.

2. Installation:

To install Ecotone Mobile, follow these steps:
Open the Google Play Store on your Android device.
Search for "Ecotone Mobile" in the search bar.
Select the Ecotone Mobile app from the search results.
Tap on the "Install" button to download and install the app on your device.
Requirements: Ecotone Mobile requires an Android device running Android OS version 4.4 (KitKat) or higher.

3. Setup:
After installing Ecotone Mobile, follow these steps to set up the app:
Open Ecotone Mobile from your device's app drawer.
Follow the on-screen prompts to grant necessary permissions (e.g., location access).
Once permissions are granted, Ecotone Mobile is ready for use.

4. Usage:
Ecotone Mobile offers the following features:
Identifying Native Plants: Use the plant identification feature to identify native plants on the OSU Cascades campus. Simply point your device's camera at the plant and follow the on-screen instructions.
Locating Sites (Plots): Use the site locator feature to locate specific sites or plots on the OSU Cascades campus. Enter the site name or coordinates to find the desired location.
Tracking Ecotone Trends: Track long-term trends of the ecotone on the OSU Cascades campus using the trend tracking functionality. View historical data and trends to analyze changes over time.

5. Troubleshooting:
If you encounter any issues while using Ecotone Mobile, try the following troubleshooting steps:
Problem: App crashes or freezes.
Solution: Close the app and restart it. If the issue persists, try restarting your device.
Problem: Unable to identify plants.
Solution: Ensure that your device's camera is functioning properly and that you have a stable internet connection.
For further assistance or support, contact the Ecotone Mobile support team at support@ecotonemobile.com.

6. Conclusion:
In conclusion, Ecotone Mobile is a valuable tool for Biology and Resource Management students at OSU Cascades. By following the instructions provided in this user guide, users can effectively utilize Ecotone Mobile to identify native plants, locate sites, and track ecotone trends on the OSU Cascades campus. Explore the app's features and make the most out of your ecological studies with Ecotone Mobile.
